# Blog Publishing Workflow

When adding a new blog post or updating an existing one, follow this workflow to ensure the post appears in both the homepage LATEST POSTS section and the sidebar navigation.

## Step 1 — Frontmatter (Required)

Every blog post file must start with a YAML frontmatter block. This is the **only thing needed** for the homepage LATEST POSTS section to auto-discover the post.

```yaml
---
title: <文章标题>
date: <YYYY-MM-DD>
description: <简短描述，用于卡片摘要>
cover: <封面图 URL>
tags:
  - <标签1>
  - <标签2>
---
```

- `title`: 文章标题，用于 LATEST POSTS 卡片和浏览器标题
- `date`: 发布日期，格式 `YYYY-MM-DD`，用于 LATEST POSTS 排序（最新优先）
- `description`: 简短描述（1-2 句话），显示在 LATEST POSTS 卡片摘要中
- `cover`: 封面图 URL，支持绝对 URL 或项目内路径（放在 `docs/public/blog/img/` 下，引用格式 `/blog/img/<文件名>`）
- `tags`: 标签数组，可选

## Step 2 — Sidebar Navigation

After the frontmatter, add the post to `docs/.vitepress/config.mts` inside `themeConfig.sidebar[0].items`:

```ts
{ text: '<显示名称>', link: '/blog/<文件名前缀>' }
```

- The link must match the URL that `import.meta.glob('docs/blog/*.md')` generates from the filename
- Filename pattern: `docs/blog/<任意名称>.md` → URL is `/blog/<任意名称>`

## Step 3 — Images (If Any)

If the post includes inline images:
1. Place image files under `docs/public/blog/img/`
2. Reference them in markdown as `/blog/img/<文件名>`

If the post references an external image for the cover, use a full HTTPS URL.

## Step 4 — Commit & Push

```bash
git add <changed files> && git commit -m "docs: <commit message>" && git push
```

Pushing to `main` automatically triggers the VitePress CI build and deploy.

## Common Mistakes

- **LATEST POSTS doesn't show a post**: Missing or malformed frontmatter `title` field — the filter requires `p.title` to be truthy
- **LATEST POSTS shows wrong URL**: The glob derives the URL from the filename. Ensure the link in `config.mts` matches the filename (without `.md`)
- **Cover image 404**: Cover must be a valid URL or a path under `docs/public/` (not `docs/blog/img/`)
- **Post not in sidebar**: Manually add an entry to `config.mts` — the sidebar is not auto-generated
